<TITLE> First flight carrying Hajj pilgrims back home lands </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)  The first flight carrying back home 315 Bangladeshi hajj pilgrims landed at Zia International Airport Monday. "I received the first batch of Bangladeshi pilgrims at ZIA, returning home after performing the hajj," religious affairs secretary Md Ataur Rahman told bdnews24.com at noon. "Another flight carrying 543 passengers is due today (Monday)," he said. "Some 85 flights have been earmarked to bring back the Bangladeshi hajis this year, with the last one to arrive on Jan 25." The flight touched down at 3:45am. Ministry officials said the first hajj flight left on Nov 12 and the last one on Dec 14. The holy rites of the hajj were performed on Dec 18. A total of 45,407 pilgrims left Bangladesh for Saudi Arabia this year, of whom 18 died over the hajj period. bdnews24.com/
